✅ Basic Syntax Rules:

* Case-sensitive (age ≠ Age)

* Statements end with ; (optional but recommended)

* Code is grouped using { }

✅ Data Types

* Primitive Types (immutable)

* string → "Hello"

* number → 10, 10.5

* boolean → true / false

* null → intentional empty value

* undefined → value not assigned

* bigint → large integers

* symbol → unique value identifiers

Non-Primitive

* object → arrays, functions, collections


js.

let name = "Naveeth";
let age = 21;
let online = true;
let skills = ["HTML", "CSS"];
